16 departments, law enforcement agencies, schools, and the United States Secret Service, Coast
17 Guard, Navy, and National Guard; and
18 WHEREAS, in the aftermath of hurricanes Debbie, Helene, and Milton, HOPE AACR
19 response teams deployed to the Florida State Operations Center in Tallahassee, supported
20 staff working at the FEMA Region IV Regional Response Coordination Center in Atlanta,
21 and assisted impacted communities in South Georgia; and
22 WHEREAS, in 2024 alone, HOPE AACR's Southeast Region logged close to 150 volunteer
23 hours and engaged in 1,200 meaningful interactions with Georgia disaster victims; and
24 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this outstanding organization be
25 appropriately honored.
26 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
27 the members of this body recognize and commend the volunteers and canines of HOPE
28 AACR (Animal-Assisted Crisis Response) for their dedicated, effective, and selfless service
29 on behalf of those in need as well as extend best wishes for continued success.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
32 HOPE AACR (Animal-Assisted Crisis Response).
